profile_positions.description:
Developing strategic marketing plans, messaging and campaigns along with associated budgets and calendars;

Provide counsel on issues raised by team of directors as a “sounding board";

Create and execute a customer focussed marketing strategy by implementing Hubspot's software and mindset for our sales & marketing activities;

Utilizing our marketing automation system Hubspot to provide efficient and effective marketing programs to drive inbound marketing leads and manage leads/accounts through the sales funnel. Work closely with sales team to ensure efficient utilization of Hubspot;

Strategic planning, developing, executing and assessing integrated, multi-channel marketing programs, including e-mail marketing, blogs, organic and paid search, video and social media;

Lead marketing efforts to promote events, driving registration and revenue goals;

Lead an in-house marketeer, including responsibility for professional development, mentoring and performance management;

Identifying and hiring third party providers and/or agencies to create content to leverage through multiple marketing campaigns and channels. This includes negotiating contracts (cost, timelines) and managing workloads;

Looking for opportunities to collaborate with partners as a way to help drive demand and generate leads, when appropriate;

Preparing and managing monthly and annual budgets for the marketing department.

In my role as Marketing Manager at the Rotterdam Marriott Hotel, I was responsible for developing and implementing marketing strategies to meet the hotel’s organizational objectives. Over the years I worked on many projects, which relate to improving the online distribution channels and online marketing activities. In 2016, I worked together with a team to rebrand The Manhattan Hotel Rotterdam to the Rotterdam Marriott Hotel. This project was internationally rewarded with Marriott's 'One team driving results' award. Watch the announcement here: https://youtu.be/JRxU2ltJmF0

